title: Tajikistan Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Tajikistan increased 7.90 percent in September of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Tajikistan averaged 12.18 percent from 1999 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 66.30 percent in December of 2000 and a record low of -2.50 percent in April of 2004. This page provides the latest reported value for - Tajikistan Food Inflation - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: National Bank of Tajikistan
